The canonical home for these rules is the demarcated section inside your project's root `AGENTS.md`.

This `.cursor/rules/karpathy-guidelines.mdc` file exists to give Cursor stronger, always-on structured enforcement (`alwaysApply: true`) while staying in sync with the universal guidelines that also apply to Claude Code, Copilot, Grok Build, and other agents.

---

**These guidelines are working when** diffs are small and focused, clarifying questions happen early, and over-engineering becomes rare.